title: For Sale:  Ruger Single Six .22, Old Model
postcontent:
To help settle an estate, I'm selling a Ruger Single Six .22 caliber revolver, old model with checkered plastic grips.  The serial number indicates that it was made in 1957.  These guns are known as the “three-screw” model or just “old models.”  It is in very good condition, with a 5 1/2" barrel, some minor holster wear, but a bright, shiny bore.  There is also a Hunter (brand) holster with the gun.

Strong, durable, dependable, and versatile, the Single-Six revolvers are the perfect small bore single-action revolver for plinking, small game hunting or even serious competition. The Single Six was first produced in June 1953.  Old Model production ended in 1972.

NOTE:  The "New Model" update has not been done to this revolver.  This is the Old Model Single Six with the 4 distinct clicks as the hammer is cocked, just like a Colt SAA.  It is recommended that you do not carry the gun with a cartridge under the hammer.  If you are a true Ruger collector, then you need this unmodified one to complete the collection and these are getting more and more scarce. 

This Ruger is mechanically perfect, and has obviously been shot very little.  It's been in storage for years, and is now available for sale.  The price of $350 is fair for an old model Ruger Single Six in this condition.  Don't be bashful.  Contact me and let's talk about this gun.  It would be the perfect Christmas present for someone special.

title: For Sale:  WASR 10/63 AK 47 7.62x39
postcontent:
I have a factory only fired Romanian WASR 10/63 AK 7.62x39 for sale.  This rifle still has some cosmoline on it.  This is the best example of a Wasr 10/63 that I have seen.  It was hand selected out of a shipment of 25 rifles that were also hand selected for quality.  The Wasr 10/63 is the premium of the Wasr AK rifles.  These are not made from the military reject parts like the Wasr 10's are, but are built in Romania from actual demilled Romanian Military rifles on new Romanian receivers with new Romanian cold hammer forged and chrome lined barrels.  Most of these like this one came from National Guard type semi-auto only rifles that rarely saw use.  The receiver has a factory rail on the side for mounting optics.  The date on the trunnion is 1970 and has the military triangle with the arrow in it indicating that it was indeed a military rifle.  The stock on this is laminated wood for durability.

This rifle barrel is threaded and has a slant brake, cleaning rod, and cleaning kit in the buttstock, and Romanian leather sling.  The bayonet lug is intact so you can affix a bayonet if you like.  Century did not build this, but did import it and changed out the necessary parts for 922r compliance such as the Tapco G2 trigger set that is now in it.

It will come with a Tapco bakelite colored 30 round magazine as well as the box, manual, and plastic oil bottle.  Included is also a Romanian metal military magazine that was included, but is beat up and non functional.  It came with the rifle but I kept it for parts.

I am asking 675 dollars for this excellent example of a WASR 10/63.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare Sig SP2009 blueline with case 2-15rd mags 9mm $$Reduced$$
postcontent:
Very nice sig sp2009 blueline for sale with law enforcement blue case and two 15rd mags. The sp2009 was only made for a few years(1999-2002) and finding a blueline 9mm model is not too easy because at the time most law enforcement was using .40 caliber. The blueline was made for law enforcement and has a cool emblem on the top of the slide. The sp2009 was the non railed predecessor to the sp2022 ,made in Switzerland when sig and sauer were just coming together. I think the non railed model looks much better as it stays more true to that classic sig look. The sig pros are every bit as durable as the p series sigs maybe even more so because the steel slide rides on beefy steel rails vs aluminum as in the p series.  They also have a better da trigger pull than the p series and are just as accurate .
was $450, now $425 firm . I will not sell for less and I wont drop the price any more. A glock is more and this is every bit as much gun for the money.

Note: condition is excellent and it has very few rds through it.

title: For Sale/Trade:  HK USP Compact
location: Wilson / Goldsboro, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
USP Compacts are smaller and lighter than large frame USPs. The reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases conceal-ability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact semiautomatic pistols that use a difficult to shoot "two-finger grip" frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floor plates. This makes the pistol easy to shoot without sacrificing conceal-ability.

Like their large frame predecessors, USP Compacts are designed with the demanding needs of the law enforcement and military shooters in mind. Using a modified link-less Browning-type action, the USP Compact is built to take the punishment of high-energy +P loads.

To reduce the length of the slide and barrel on the USP Compact, the mechanical recoil reduction system found on large frame USPs has been replaced by a specially designed flat compression spring contained in the captive recoil spring assembly by a polymer absorber bushing. Service life is still engineered to exceed 20,000 rounds.

Easy to shoot, case, three 13 round magazines, night sights and simple to maintain; the USP Compact is a reliable, safe, accurate, and highly concealable pistol.

Included is a Streamlight TLR 3
